H3.text: what is the name of the protease which is released in the stomach. Pepsin

A4.text: Pepsin is one of the main digestive enzymes in the digestive systems of humans and many other animals, where it helps digest the proteins in food.

A5.text: Pepsin's zymogen (proenzyme), pepsinogen, is released by the gastric chief cells in the stomach wall, and upon mixing with the hydrochloric acid of the gastric juice, pepsinogen activates to become pepsin.
